Super Mario 64 (スーパーマリオ64, Sūpā Mario Rokujūyon) is a platform game developed by Nintendo Entertainment Analysis and Development and published by Nintendo for the Nintendo 64.
Information about Super Mario 64 first leaked out in November 1995, and a playable version of the game was presented days later as part of the world premiere for the Nintendo 64 (then known as the "Ultra 64") at Nintendo Space World.
Super Mario 64 has been commercially successful; it was the best-selling Nintendo 64 game.
